00:08:40.730 --> 00:08:42.790
I think it will be
great to hear the story

00:08:42.790 --> 00:08:45.000
of you know, a little
bit more about.

00:08:45.000 --> 00:08:49.330
&gt;&gt; Yeah, well eyam is
actually a little village

00:08:49.330 --> 00:08:51.970
in England, not in Ireland.

00:08:51.970 --> 00:08:58.460 position:56%
But it's one I read about around
the time I started writing the first

00:08:58.460 --> 00:09:00.270
piece for Carol.

00:09:00.270 --> 00:09:03.070
And it's just this tiny village

00:09:03.070 --> 00:09:08.050
that the plague was discovered
there in the 16th Century.

00:09:08.050 --> 00:09:11.790
And this tiny village decided
to kind of blockade itself

00:09:11.790 --> 00:09:18.310 position:56%
in from the rest of the world rather
than letting the plague spread

00:09:18.310 --> 00:09:20.070
to the outside the village.

00:09:20.070 --> 00:09:23.960
So I just took it as a
metaphor really in terms

00:09:23.960 --> 00:09:25.790 position:56%
of what I was talking about earlier.

00:09:25.790 --> 00:09:31.590
These different kind of colors,
parts of the contrabass clarinet

00:09:31.590 --> 00:09:35.710
that I really wanted to zone
in on and kind of isolate them

00:09:35.710 --> 00:09:39.020
and then eventually
let them kind of spread

00:09:39.020 --> 00:09:42.360 position:56%
and become one kind of bigger place.

00:09:42.360 --> 00:09:47.530
So it was really just
a metaphor that I used

00:09:47.530 --> 00:09:51.060
to get my mind moving I guess.

00:09:51.060 --> 00:09:56.430 position:56%
But what's, I never actually visited
the village but I've been working

00:09:56.430 --> 00:10:00.150
on these pieces since
I said, like 2008.

00:10:00.150 --> 00:10:02.060
And I always said, when I finish,

00:10:02.060 --> 00:10:05.060
the whole five pieces
then I'll go and visit.

00:10:05.060 --> 00:10:10.940 position:56%
Because I only live in Ireland which
is like a short plane away from,

00:10:10.940 --> 00:10:14.250
like an hour flight
