00:27:09.900 --> 00:27:14.500
Like, you can have like you
know, half air, half tone

00:27:14.500 --> 00:27:18.840
and then much more air and
that's still very pitched.

00:27:18.840 --> 00:27:24.280
So for me in terms of talking about
timbre which really means color,

00:27:24.280 --> 00:27:28.860
you know, there's so many different
shades you can get of one note,

00:27:28.860 --> 00:27:35.850
say of like you know, middle
C. You can hear that with air,

00:27:35.850 --> 00:27:39.020
with a little bit of
pitch, with full pitch,

00:27:39.020 --> 00:27:43.170
with a kind of percussive
slap, with a key click.

00:27:43.170 --> 00:27:46.910
You know, the pitch is present
