&gt;&gt; I'll give a really short answer.

00:30:37.670 --> 00:30:42.970
I, I, because I think
it's actually very common.

00:30:42.970 --> 00:30:46.320
I was trained as a classical
musician and I had a crisis

00:30:46.320 --> 00:30:50.540
and that was the way
out of the crisis.

00:30:50.540 --> 00:30:53.130
Yeah, I think and I
really think that maybe

00:30:53.130 --> 00:30:55.860
that may be the majority of people.

00:30:55.860 --> 00:31:03.360
I think that you know, classical
music is, the music is sublime and

00:31:03.360 --> 00:31:07.750
yet there are constraints
about it that make it very hard

00:31:07.750 --> 00:31:10.600
to find one's own place in it.

00:31:10.600 --> 00:31:13.300
And I'll leave it at that, yeah.

00:31:13.300 --> 00:31:19.670
&gt;&gt; I guess and another
I think very common way

00:31:19.670 --> 00:31:23.030
of becoming a composer is kind of
falling into it by accident is.

00:31:23.030 --> 00:31:25.040
[ Laughter ]

00:31:25.040 --> 00:31:26.340
&gt;&gt; Becoming anything.

00:31:26.340 --> 00:31:33.770
&gt;&gt; Yeah. Like I didn't, I kind of
ended up in a composition class

00:31:33.770 --> 00:31:39.180
