and Breaking Instruments.

00:32:23.590 --> 00:32:28.760
And the first piece I heard
was Berio Sequenza for voice

00:32:28.760 --> 00:32:32.230
and like I really hadn't
grown up around composers.

00:32:32.230 --> 00:32:36.100
I really didn't even know that
there was still living composers.

00:32:36.100 --> 00:32:42.000
So the, when I heard Berio
Sequenza for voice I was just,

00:32:42.000 --> 00:32:44.810
it felt like a new
world that opened.

00:32:44.810 --> 00:32:49.360
And I just kept composing
from there really.

00:32:49.360 --> 00:32:54.780
But it was something that
suddenly appeared and it kind of,

00:32:54.780 --> 00:32:58.730
I mean looking back it makes
sense to me that it you know,

00:32:58.730 --> 00:33:00.920
I've always wanted to
do something with music

00:33:00.920 --> 00:33:03.880
